Detailed Description

cvmx_l2c_dbg

L2C_DBG = L2C DEBUG Register

Description: L2C Tag/Data Store Debug Register

Notes: (1) When using the L2T, L2D or FINV Debug probe feature, the LDD command WILL NOT update the DuTags. (2) L2T, L2D, FINV MUST BE mutually exclusive (only one set) (3) Force Invalidate is intended as a means for SW to invalidate the L2 Cache while also writing back dirty data to memory to maintain coherency. (4) L2 Cache Lock Down feature MUST BE disabled (L2C_LCKBASE[LCK_ENA]=0) if ANY of the L2C debug features (L2T, L2D, FINV) are enabled.
